This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with adversarial attacks on deep neural networks for perception tasks. It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories as it involves the use of deep neural networks and machine learning techniques. The paper also discusses the security and cryptography aspects of adversarial attacks, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. Finally, the paper proposes a new technique for crafting adversarial examples, which could place it in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
